        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 8:22PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 11 miles north of Amidon, or 29 miles southwest of
Dickinson, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amidon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
